title: V01 — Comprehensive playthrough (blank-output sweep)
story: familyzoo
author: Sharpee Tutorial
description: Exercise v01's command surface to flag blank/silent responses or other engine glitches in the simplest possible Sharpee story.

---

# === Documented commands from the tutorial ===

> look
[OK: contains "Zoo Entrance"]

> examine sign
[OK: contains "WELCOME"]

> examine booth
[OK: contains "Self-Guided"]

> take sign
[OK: contains "fixed in place"]

# Engine-variant lottery — stdlib's inventory action picks one of 4 message
# IDs at random when empty (inventory.js:104). "carry" matches the two
# "carrying anything" variants but misses "hands are empty" / "pockets are
# empty". Use contains_any so any picked variant satisfies the assertion.
# See CLAUDE.md → Testing for the two-layer model and the dedicated
# variant-coverage transcript.
> inventory
[OK: contains_any "carry" "empty"]

# === Aliases — should resolve to scenery ===

> examine wooden sign
[OK: contains "WELCOME"]

> examine welcome sign
[OK: contains "WELCOME"]

> examine window
[OK: contains "Self-Guided"]

> x sign

> x booth

